{
  "stem": "1132.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there is simply nothing that works.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There is no normalcy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, I think the memory that I've got and what we need to think about is total abnormalcy and nothing the way that one would expect.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Even though-- even when I survived, I survived-- and that was out of the normal, because most people in my situation did not survive.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So surviving and surviving under the circumstances was out of the ordinary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And surviving with my parents and my sister was also out of the ordinary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I know that there was always a lot of talk as to what happened to my cousin, the cousin who was killed at Theresienstadt, that's where-- either Bergen-Belsen or to Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were never knew-- sure which one she ended up at.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were sightings of her at both, so we obviously never knew what happened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that you knew that all of a sudden you had a favorite cousin, and that favorite cousin is no longer there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, this was a cousin who was about a dozen years older than I was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was all-- again, somebody else who babied me, and she disappeared.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it's really a confluence of the out of the normal, out of the ordinary, watching buildings being bombed, watching people that you know and you love disappear, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] knowing that something awful is happening, but not really knowing what is happening.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, how much does a little kid really understand?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Knowing that something terrible is going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And always looking at your mother who is always worrying and always holding onto you like your-- her life is depending on you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's exactly what she was doing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "OK, we're about done with this tape.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Who is that?",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
